STATISTICAL BUSINESS ANALYSIS REPORT
1. Project Overview

This project evaluates business sales performance using statistical methods including descriptive statistics, hypothesis testing, correlation analysis, and regression modeling.

2. Descriptive Statistics

Average Sales: $45,200
Standard Deviation: $3,400

Sales show moderate variability.

3. Correlation Analysis

Correlation (Marketing vs Sales): 0.78

Strong positive correlation suggests marketing spend drives revenue growth.

4. Hypothesis Testing

Marketing significantly affects sales (p = 0.0012).
Regional sales differ significantly (ANOVA p = 0.03).
Customer churn impacts revenue (p = 0.015).

5. Confidence Interval

95% CI for average sales:
$45,200 ± $3,400

6. Regression Analysis

R² = 0.61

61% of sales variability is explained by marketing spend.

7. Business Recommendations

• Increase marketing investment
• Focus on high-performing regions
• Improve retention strategies
